(.6) 08 May 2006

  What is new ?
  ---------------------
  #79, option to request login code for human verification (/HVC ON)
  #85, missing NoSpamExitMsg option will crash the ircd

(.5) 07 Jan 2006

  What is new ?
  ---------------------
  #57: DefaultChanMode option to define default channel modes
  #55: super vlines should be checked on away messages
  #32:  configure --enable-halfops option to enable half-ops
  0000346: WebPass option to be used by webchat clients  
  Add rehash script to the tools dir

  What has been fixed ?
  ---------------------
  #13 : chanserv identify is now removed from /identify
  #51 : Compiling now works on x64 systems
  #6 : /msg botserv displays garbage  
  0000347: supersvlines should use match patterns
  0000324: PIDFILE location is now used when specific location is given


(.4) 27 Aug 2005

  What is new ?
  ---------------------
  0000313: configure option to enable/disable flood delay
  0000301: super svlines
  0000263: chghost command for remote hostname change
  0000260: utf-8 support on nicks and chan names
  Added reconf.sh script to call autoconf
  GLineOnSVline: new dconf option to automaticly gline who trigger a svline

  What has been fixed ?
  ---------------------
  0000292: crash if removing +o from users without o:line
  0000289: crash on SVSJOIN/SVSPART with missing parameter
  0000286: gline #chan crash on a rare condition
  0000264: compilation with gcc4 fails

(.3) 28 Jan 2005

  What is new ?
  ---------------------
  0000184: CryptKey dconf option replaced services timestamp for spoofing
  0000186: Add /ns, /cs, /os etc. as services aliases

  What has been fixed ?
  ---------------------
  0000189: Incorrect message source on debug option (-d) logs
  0000182: -d was adedd to the invalid syntax message
  0000190: If CryptKey is disabled keep using old situation of randomness

(.2) 11 Dec 2004

  What has been fixed ?
  ---------------------
  0000181: remove unused SCS code
  0000171: remove the auto-away when the idle time is over
  0000177: Do not allow "\" to be used on nicks, chans and usernames

(.1) 13 Nov 2004

  What is new ?
  ---------------------
  0000162: domain stats
  0000167: MaxOperIdleTime
  0000168: AutoAwayIdleTime

  What has been fixed ?
  ---------------------
  0000170: StrongVlines option should be removed
  0000164: AutoJoinChan with multiple chans only works for first user
  0000166: strip colors instead of blocking them on chanmode +c
  0000163: PTS4.txt out of date

  PTlink6.19.0 (05 Nov 2004)
==================================================================

  What is new ?
  ---------------------
  Issue 0000151: AutoJoinChan dconf option
  Issue 0000144: MaxChansPerRegUser to specify maxchans for registered users
  Issue 0000130: Protocol change to use SNICK/SSJOIN on netjoins
  Issue 0000143: killircd tool to be used on windows version
  Issue 0000128: command line debug option

  What has been fixed ?
  ---------------------
  Issue 0000120: warning compiling with ipv6 support
  Issue 0000133: SVLINES should filter words on AWAY reasons
  Issue 0000135: GLineOnExcessFlood is a timed option
  Issue 0000136: dconf now use macros
  Issue 0000091: fixed again (old fix wasn't even compiling) 

